* text=auto

# Vendored, version-pinned third-party assets: store and check out byte-for-byte
# (no EOL normalization) so the on-disk bytes match the recorded upstream SHA256
# in THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md. `* text=auto` was rewriting the minified bundle to
# CRLF on Windows checkout, diverging it from the pristine upstream LF bytes.
src/App/web/vendor/** -text

# Same protection for the throwaway spike bundles (spikes/*/web/vendor): a vendored
# minified binary must never be EOL-rewritten by `* text=auto`. Not shipped, but
# keeps spikes reproducible and pre-empts the "new vendored binary without -text"
# supply-chain finding-class.
spikes/**/web/vendor/** -text
